creator: Rosanna Eleanor Leprohon
description: LibriVox volunteers bring you 8 recordings of The Hunter and His Dying Steed by Rosanna Eleanor Leprohon. This was the Fortnightly Poetry project for February 15, 2015. Read in English by DomBombadil; Claudia Salto; Ezwa; Greg Giordano; Larry Wilson; Leonard Wilson; Maria Kasper and RLC. Rosanna Eleanor Leprohon, born Rosanna Eleanor Mullins, was a Canadian writer and poet. She was "one of the first English-Canadian writers to depict French Canada in a way that earned the praise of, and resulted in her novels being read by, both anglophone and francophone Canadians." (Summary from Wikipedia) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
